The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Riding Abhijit Gangulys unbeaten 55, Sporting Union defeated Young Bengal by eight wickets in a CAB two-day league match here on Sunday. 

 ITC A defeated Tata Steel by four wickets in The Telegraph Merchants Cup at the CCFC on Sunday. In reply to Tata Steels 59/4, ITC A reached 62 losing just two wickets.

 The CAB, at a function Monday, will convey its best wishes to former Team India captain Sourav Ganguly for the World Cup. 

 CHESS: Calcutta Open at the Alekhine Chess Club, Gorky Sadan, from 2 pm.

 CRICKET: The Telegraph Merchants Cup at CC amp;FC from 5.30pm

 GENERAL: Indo-Bangla Games at the Salt Lake Stadium from 9 am




